<item>
            <title>[SPARK-7788] Streaming | Kinesis | KinesisReceiver blocks in onStart</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7788</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;KinesisReceiver calls worker.run() which is a blocking call (while loop) as per source code of kinesis-client library - &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/blob/v1.2.1/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/kinesis/clientlibrary/lib/worker/Worker.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/blob/v1.2.1/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/kinesis/clientlibrary/lib/worker/Worker.java&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in infinite loop while calling sparkStreamingContext.stop(stopSparkContext = false, stopGracefully = true) perhaps because ReceiverTracker is never able to register the receiver (it&apos;s receiverInfo field is a empty map) causing it to be stuck in infinite loop while waiting for running flag to be set to false. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, we should investigate a way to have receiver restart in case of failures. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
